<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <a href="#CITEREFLarson2004" title="">Larson 2004</a>, p.&#160;258 "Virtually no secular scientists accepted the doctrines of <a href="/wiki/Creation_science" title="Creation science">creation science</a>; but that did not deter creation scientists from advancing scientific arguments for their position." See also <a href="#CITEREFMartzMcDaniel1987" title="">Martz &amp; McDaniel 1987</a>, p.&#160;23, a Newsweek article which states "By one count there are some 700 scientists (out of a total of 480,000 U.S. earth and life scientists) who give credence to creation-science, the general theory that complex life forms did not evolve but appeared 'abruptly'."</li>
